A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a chaotic classroom scene where a small child sits smugly on an oversized throne-like desk chair, arms crossed defiantly, while a frazzled adult teacher kneels beside the desk in a pleading posture with hands clasped together. The classroom is in disarray with paper airplanes mid-flight, overturned chairs, and other children running wild in the background. The color palette features muted pastels with pops of red and gold, rendered in the style of mid-century educational posters with slightly exaggerated proportions and soft halftone texturing. The child wears a small golden crown askew on their head, emphasizing the role reversal. Warm afternoon light streams through large windows, casting long dramatic shadows across the wooden floor.
